=========== Installer llvm+clang ==================
To compile stylecheck you need to install LLVM & CLANG as well has the developement headers.

Stylecheck is using llvm/clang from svn revision: 211571
To compile llvm/clang you can follow the step-by-step procedure available there (specifying the adequate revision number):
http://clang.llvm.org/

Once llvm & clang are working and install on your system you can compile
stylecheck using the following procedure
========== Compiler stylecheck ====================
# cd YOURSOFAROOT
# mkdir tools/stylechecker-build
# cd tools/stylechecker-build 
# cmake ../stylechecker
# make
# make install 

clang requires some specific header so you must either:
	- install stylecheck in the same directory as where is installed clang  (eg. using make install)

	- install the requested header "../" where is located the stylecheck.exe  application.
	You can find more infos on this issue at section "Builtin includes"
	http://clang.llvm.org/docs/LibTooling.html

========== Tester stylecheck ====================
# cd YOURSOFAROOT
# cd tools/stylechecker/
# stylecheck.exe test1.cpp  --

========== Wrapper stylecheck dans  un script de build ====================

---------- dans un script fakegcc.sh mettre ----------
#!/bin/bash

FILENAME_SRC=${BASH_ARGV[0]}
FILENAME_OUT=${BASH_ARGV[2]}

PATH_TO_STYLECHECK_DIR/stylecheck.exe $FILENAME_SRC -- $@
g++ $@

------------------------------------------------


Et après il faut faire une nouveau répertoire de build sofa.
mkdir build-sofa-stylecheck
cd build-sofa-stylecheck  
CXX=pathto/fakegcc.sh CC=pathto/fakegcc.sh cmake pathto/sofa-src
